cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with computer vision tasks related to face images, specifically super-resolution and facial landmark detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of GANs and deep learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with image processing, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of optimization techniques and loss functions could suggest it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
